00:33:08,153 --> 00:33:09,703
Thank you.

265
00:33:12,357 --> 00:33:13,997
Can anyone tell me
what this flower is?

266
00:33:14,292 --> 00:33:15,282
I know this scent.

267
00:33:15,527 --> 00:33:17,927
Si senorita. It's called Romneya.

268
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:20,139
But it only grows in California.

269
00:33:20,499 --> 00:33:23,079
And I believe
this is your first visit to our shores.

270
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:24,732
Yes.

271
00:33:54,766 --> 00:33:56,316
More whiskey.

272
00:33:58,003 --> 00:33:59,703
Or whatever you call this.

273
00:34:00,005 --> 00:34:01,905
I don't want to see the bottom
of this glass, eh?

274
00:34:02,274 --> 00:34:03,353
Money first.

275
00:34:03,575 --> 00:34:05,035
Money first.

276
00:34:07,812 --> 00:34:10,002
Wait, wait, wait.

277
00:34:12,183 --> 00:34:13,523
What about this?

278
00:34:14,252 --> 00:34:15,241
Silver.

279
00:34:16,388 --> 00:34:19,348
Of course, silver. The finest.

280
00:34:25,996 --> 00:34:27,366
Where did you get that?

281
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:29,569
It's none of your business.

282
00:34:30,835 --> 00:34:32,125
Where did you get it?

283
00:34:35,873 --> 00:34:37,863
It was my brother's.

284
00:34:39,143 --> 00:34:40,754
He's dead.

285
00:34:43,447 --> 00:34:44,937
I'm sorry.

286
00:34:45,216 --> 00:34:46,326
You're sorry?

287
00:34:46,952 --> 00:34:48,792
Why should you be sorry?

288
00:34:50,855 --> 00:34:53,815
You should not trade something
like that for a mere glass of whiskey.

289
00:34:54,292 --> 00:34:55,522
Why not?

290
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,490
You think I could get two?

291
00:35:05,337 --> 00:35:06,707
Who's that?

292
00:35:11,676 --> 00:35:13,046
That's the man who killed my brother.

293
00:35:13,345 --> 00:35:14,194
You're drunk and you're angry,

294
00:35:14,412 --> 00:35:16,721
in no condition to fight
a professional soldier.

295
00:35:17,949 --> 00:35:19,999
Get out of my way, old man.

296
00:35:50,615 --> 00:35:52,165
Would you care to try again?

297
00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:55,515
You're welcome.

298
00:35:58,123 --> 00:35:59,553
For what?

299
00:36:00,258 --> 00:36:02,008
For saving your life.

300
00:36:06,064 --> 00:36:06,964
I would have killed him.

301
00:36:07,198 --> 00:36:09,808
No, not today. He is trained to kill.

302
00:36:10,669 --> 00:36:12,158
You seem trained to drink.

303
00:36:12,437 --> 00:36:13,167
Yes, my friend,

304
00:36:13,338 --> 00:36:15,558
you would have fought very bravely
and died very quickly.

305
00:36:15,974 --> 00:36:17,704
Who, then,
would avenge your brother?

306
00:36:20,111 --> 00:36:21,810
[ would have found a way.

307
00:36:22,681 --> 00:36:24,231
I've never lost a fight.

308
00:36:24,516 --> 00:36:26,536
Except to a crippled old man,
just now.

309
00:36:28,486 --> 00:36:29,716
What is your name?

310
00:36:30,488 --> 00:36:33,067
-Alejandro.
-Alejandro.

311
00:36:35,694 --> 00:36:37,974
You know there is a saying,
a very old saying...

312
00:36:38,396 --> 00:36:40,446
"When the pupil is ready,
the master will appear."

313
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:41,759
Now, if you want to kill this man,

314
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,520
I can help you
and I can teach you how.

315
00:36:43,802 --> 00:36:44,532
How to move, how to think,

316
00:36:44,703 --> 00:36:46,753
how to take your revenge
with honor and...

317
00:36:47,105 --> 00:36:48,335
live to celebrate it.

318
00:36:48,573 --> 00:36:49,803
But it will take dedication.

319
00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:51,531
It will take time.

320
00:36:51,976 --> 00:36:53,786
Why are you so eager to help me?

321
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:56,792
Because once, a long time ago...

322
00:37:00,351 --> 00:37:02,341
you did the same for me.

323
00:37:12,864 --> 00:37:14,474
I can't believe it.

324
00:37:16,101 --> 00:37:18,061
I never thought that one day...

325
00:37:18,503 --> 00:37:21,223
] would be standing
in the lair of the fox.

326
00:37:22,373 --> 00:37:24,103
In the lair of Zorro.

327
00:37:24,943 --> 00:37:28,843
Yeah...this place was devoted
to the training of Zorro.

328
00:37:31,316 --> 00:37:33,125
Where were you all these years?

329
00:37:33,485 --> 00:37:35,125
I thought you were dead.

330
00:37:36,855 --> 00:37:38,665
I was dead...

331
00:37:39,457 --> 00:37:41,537
and we will leave it at that.

332
00:37:48,466 --> 00:37:51,156
l remember last time I saw you,
in the square.

333
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:53,623
Fighting a hundred men.

334
00:37:53,905 --> 00:37:55,605
-A hundred men?
-l cannot forget.

335
00:37:55,907 --> 00:37:58,127
You were the greatest swordsman
who zer lived.

336
00:37:58,543 --> 00:37:59,943
Yes.

337
00:38:00,245 --> 00:38:02,875
Rafael Montero was the governor
of California then.

338
00:38:04,048 --> 00:38:05,718
Do you remember him?

339
00:38:07,652 --> 00:38:08,912
What?

340
00:38:09,687 --> 00:38:12,237
Rafael Montero,
do you remember him?

341
00:38:14,092 --> 00:38:17,342
Yes...his soldiers killed many...

342
00:38:17,862 --> 00:38:20,882
and, he was the sworn enemy
of Zorro.

343
00:38:22,167 --> 00:38:23,397
You.

344
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:25,167
Montero's come back.

345
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:26,332
Good.

346
00:38:26,571 --> 00:38:27,621
Then you can kill him.

347
00:38:27,839 --> 00:38:29,449
No, there are...complications,

348
00:38:29,741 --> 00:38:32,111
too many complications
for me to ignore.

349
00:38:33,444 --> 00:38:34,814
What complications?

350
00:38:42,187 --> 00:38:44,557
I can see we're not gonna spend
much time talking.

351
00:38:46,925 --> 00:38:48,765
Montero has some plan, some...

352
00:38:49,127 --> 00:38:50,237
design for California.

353
00:38:50,461 --> 00:38:51,660
Otherwise,
he would not have retained

354
00:38:51,896 --> 00:38:53,766
the services of your Captain Love.

355
00:38:54,465 --> 00:38:56,365
We must find out what that design is.

356
00:38:56,734 --> 00:38:57,964
And then what?

357
00:38:59,137 --> 00:39:00,477
If you are ready...

358
00:39:01,039 --> 00:39:03,209
we will both tempt our fates.

359
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:05,298
Let's go then!

360
00:39:10,215 --> 00:39:11,885
Do you know how to use that thing?

361
00:39:13,051 --> 00:39:14,221
Yes.

362
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:16,292
The pointy end goes
into the other man.

363
00:39:18,790 --> 00:39:20,310
Yeah.

364
00:39:20,792 --> 00:39:22,781
This is going to take a lot of work.

365
00:39:24,796 --> 00:39:28,136
This is called a training circle,
a master's wheel.

366
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:32,020
This circle will be your world,
your whole life.

367
00:39:33,104 --> 00:39:35,794
Until I tell you otherwise,
there is nothing outside of it.

368
00:39:36,307 --> 00:39:40,207
-Capitan Love is out...
-There is nothing...outside of it.

369
00:39:40,845 --> 00:39:43,944
Captain Love does not exist
until l say he exists.

370
00:39:49,854 --> 00:39:52,314
As your skill
with the sword improves...

371
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:55,334
you will progress to a...smaller circle.

372
00:39:55,994 --> 00:39:57,724
With each new circle,
your world contracts,

373
00:39:58,029 --> 00:39:59,759
bringing you that much closer
to your adversary,

374
00:40:00,098 --> 00:40:02,087
that much closer to retribution.

375
00:40:03,468 --> 00:40:05,198
I like that part.

376
00:40:06,104 --> 00:40:07,364
Shall we?

377
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:29,960
Slow!

378
00:40:30,662 --> 00:40:32,002
Attack slow.

379
00:40:32,297 --> 00:40:33,467
Attack!

380
00:40:33,698 --> 00:40:35,368
Slow. Again!

381
00:40:35,667 --> 00:40:36,747
Slow!

382
00:40:36,968 --> 00:40:40,308
Let's try and...slow, like...Good.

383
00:40:41,539 --> 00:40:43,969
Good...that is good.

384
00:40:44,375 --> 00:40:45,105
Thank you.

385
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:46,145
Attack.

386
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:51,118
Good.

387
00:40:53,685 --> 00:40:54,855
Time for a drink.

388
00:41:07,765 --> 00:41:10,015
Perfect. Do it again.

389
00:41:27,385 --> 00:41:29,055
One, five, three!

390
00:41:31,122 --> 00:41:32,491
Six, four, two!

391
00:41:33,725 --> 00:41:35,275
And lunge!

392
00:41:36,561 --> 00:41:37,701
Over-lunged!

393
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:48,128
Lesson number one...

394
00:41:48,406 --> 00:41:50,246
never attack in anger.

395
00:41:55,947 --> 00:41:57,587
Lesson number two...

396
00:41:59,283 --> 00:42:00,543
Come with me.

397
00:42:03,955 --> 00:42:05,035
What?

398
00:42:18,503 --> 00:42:20,313
So what is lesson number three?

399
00:42:20,705 --> 00:42:22,694
To get to lesson number four.

400
00:42:44,829 --> 00:42:45,909
Again?

401
00:42:55,640 --> 00:42:57,569
Montero!

402
00:43:08,786 --> 00:43:10,126
A black Andalusian.

403
00:43:10,421 --> 00:43:11,790
Magnificent.

404
00:43:12,657 --> 00:43:14,437
Looks like your old horse, Tornado.

405
00:43:15,126 --> 00:43:16,266
Who's that?

406
00:43:53,531 --> 00:43:55,081
Quiet, quiet.

407
00:44:06,711 --> 00:44:07,910
Damn horse!

408
00:44:08,146 --> 00:44:09,316
What are you doing, huh?

409
00:44:09,547 --> 00:44:11,277
What are you doing?

410
00:44:13,885 --> 00:44:15,585
I'll see you tonight.

411
00:44:37,875 --> 00:44:41,185
Zorro, you look better than ever.

412
00:45:07,605 --> 00:45:09,715
Be careful, senorita.

413
00:45:10,308 --> 00:45:12,358
There are dangerous men about.

414
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:17,050
Well, if you see any,
be sure to point them out.

415
00:46:08,466 --> 00:46:10,016
Okay, everybody's in.

416
00:46:10,301 --> 00:46:11,561
Don Burrite...

417
00:46:32,990 --> 00:46:34,509
Listen.

418
00:46:35,092 --> 00:46:38,842
I'm going to give you the great honor
of being my horse.

419
00:46:57,415 --> 00:47:00,345
We are...like one spirit.

420
00:47:06,090 --> 00:47:09,020
Damn it! Stop!

421
00:48:05,383 --> 00:48:07,113
Go, go...go, go!

422
00:48:39,383 --> 00:48:40,582
Get him!

423
00:50:40,437 --> 00:50:41,457
Kill him.

424
00:51:18,542 --> 00:51:19,241
Zorro!

425
00:51:19,410 --> 00:51:21,140
The legend has returned!

426
00:52:02,019 --> 00:52:03,308
Don't yell.

427
00:52:07,024 --> 00:52:08,334
I need sanctuary, Father.

428
00:52:08,626 --> 00:52:11,286
-You don't know me, so...
-Zorro? Of course I know you.

429
00:52:11,762 --> 00:52:13,632
Zorro, is it really you?

430
00:52:13,998 --> 00:52:14,788
I must say the years

431
00:52:14,965 --> 00:52:16,365
have been far kinder to you
than they have been to me.

432
00:52:16,667 --> 00:52:18,717
I'm sorry,
I have no time for talk now.

433
00:52:19,069 --> 00:52:21,999
Father, please...hide me.

434
00:52:22,806 --> 00:52:24,176
Come.

435
00:52:28,712 --> 00:52:30,552
Just like the old days.

436
00:52:39,289 --> 00:52:40,959
Padre, is that you?

437
00:52:42,593 --> 00:52:43,613
Padre, is everything all right?

438
00:52:43,861 --> 00:52:46,051
It sounds like there is a battle
going on out there.

439
00:52:47,398 --> 00:52:49,148
Don't worry, my dear.

440
00:52:49,600 --> 00:52:52,060
You are safe in the house of the Lord.

441
00:52:52,703 --> 00:52:54,433
Of course, Padre.

442
00:52:55,339 --> 00:52:56,979
Forgive me, Father,
for have sinned.

443
00:52:57,274 --> 00:52:59,384
It has been three days
since my last confession.

444
00:52:59,743 --> 00:53:00,473
Three days.

445
00:53:00,644 --> 00:53:02,314
How many sins could you have
committed in three days?

446
00:53:02,613 --> 00:53:04,692
Come back
when you've had more time, please.

447
00:53:05,816 --> 00:53:06,716
Excuse me?

448
00:53:08,419 --> 00:53:09,788
Listen, senorita...

449
00:53:13,290 --> 00:53:17,100
please...go on.

450
00:53:18,095 --> 00:53:20,404
I have broken
the Fourth Commandment, Padre.

451
00:53:21,665 --> 00:53:22,515
You killed somebody?

452
00:53:22,733 --> 00:53:24,633
No, that is not
the Fourth Commandment.

453
00:53:25,869 --> 00:53:27,179
Of course not.

454
00:53:27,471 --> 00:53:32,451
You...in what way did you break
the most sacred...

455
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:34,640
..of commandments?

456
00:53:34,945 --> 00:53:36,675
I dishonored my father.

457
00:53:38,382 --> 00:53:40,052
That is not so bad.

458
00:53:40,350 --> 00:53:41,839
Maybe your father deserved it.

459
00:53:42,152 --> 00:53:43,322
What did you say?

460
00:53:44,354 --> 00:53:48,394
I said, tell me more...my child.

461
00:53:49,159 --> 00:53:52,969
Well, I try to behave properly,
the way my father would like me to.

462
00:53:53,864 --> 00:53:56,264
But I'm afraid my heart is too wild.

463
00:53:56,900 --> 00:53:58,270
Too wild?

464
00:53:58,569 --> 00:53:59,469
Yes.

465
00:53:59,703 --> 00:54:02,743
Could you be a little more specific
about that?

466
00:54:03,273 --> 00:54:05,553
I had impure thoughts about a man.

467
00:54:06,076 --> 00:54:08,736
I did.
I think he was a bandit or something.

468
00:54:09,213 --> 00:54:11,463
He wore a black mask.

469
00:54:12,916 --> 00:54:16,316
He had a...a deep voice?

470
00:54:17,588 --> 00:54:18,878
Yes.

471
00:54:19,256 --> 00:54:21,216
Ruggedly handsome?

472
00:54:21,592 --> 00:54:24,022
I do not know.
His face was half covered.

473
00:54:25,662 --> 00:54:28,622
But something
in his eyes captured me.

474
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:30,389
Captured you?

475
00:54:30,667 --> 00:54:34,237
l felt warm and feverish.

476
00:54:35,572 --> 00:54:37,302
Lustful?

477
00:54:40,377 --> 00:54:42,107
Yes, lustful.

478
00:54:45,682 --> 00:54:47,491
Forgive me.

479
00:54:51,855 --> 00:54:53,435
l forgive you.

480
00:54:57,995 --> 00:54:59,725
Look over there, by the altar!

481
00:55:02,900 --> 00:55:03,890
Search everything!

482
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:07,914
The chapel, the loft,
the rectory...all of it!

483
00:55:08,505 --> 00:55:10,645
This is a house of God.

484
00:55:11,708 --> 00:55:12,438
Don't worry, Padre.

485
00:55:12,609 --> 00:55:14,779
We'll be gone by the time
He gets back.

486
00:55:17,447 --> 00:55:18,647
Senorita...

487
00:55:19,349 --> 00:55:21,079
..you have done nothing wrong.

488
00:55:21,418 --> 00:55:25,668
The only sin would be to deny
what your heart truly feels.

489
00:55:27,057 --> 00:55:28,486
Now go!

490
00:55:31,995 --> 00:55:33,575
Elena!

491
00:55:39,036 --> 00:55:40,206
What are you doing here?

492
00:55:40,437 --> 00:55:41,727
I was confessing.

493
00:55:42,306 --> 00:55:44,036
-Confessing?
-Yes.

494
00:55:45,008 --> 00:55:47,178
To whom? The priest is here.

495
00:55:50,814 --> 00:55:52,214
Stand back, Elena.

496
00:55:53,417 --> 00:55:54,647
Please.

497
00:56:13,337 --> 00:56:15,677
Out of respect for Miss Montero...

498
00:56:16,573 --> 00:56:18,562
I'll deal with you later.

499
00:56:26,884 --> 00:56:28,194
Horse!

500
00:56:28,852 --> 00:56:30,312
Come here.

501
00:56:35,025 --> 00:56:36,165
Blackie!

502
00:56:36,393 --> 00:56:37,703
Thunder!

503
00:56:38,862 --> 00:56:39,762
Storm!

504
00:56:39,997 --> 00:56:42,777
Stupido, get over here now!

505
00:56:44,835 --> 00:56:48,435
I warn you...I'll get another horse.

506
00:57:58,008 --> 00:58:01,288
So...what do you think?

507
00:58:06,149 --> 00:58:07,899
Sir, sir!

508
00:58:08,251 --> 00:58:09,561
I got the black stallion.

509
00:58:09,853 --> 00:58:11,583
I carved a "2" in the...

510
00:58:13,991 --> 00:58:14,841
Don...Diego,

511
00:58:15,058 --> 00:58:17,368
the people will be speaking
the name of Zorro again.

512
00:58:17,794 --> 00:58:18,614
You think stealing a horse

513
00:58:18,795 --> 00:58:19,965
and scratching marks
in a wall makes you

514
00:58:20,197 --> 00:58:23,127
worthy enough to wear that mask?

515
00:58:25,769 --> 00:58:27,198
Be careful.

516
00:58:30,907 --> 00:58:32,777
You're a thief, Alejandro.

517
00:58:33,143 --> 00:58:34,893
A pitiful clown.

518
00:58:35,779 --> 00:58:37,179
Zorro was a servant of the people.

519
00:58:37,481 --> 00:58:39,531
He was not a seeker of fame,
like you.

520
00:58:41,418 --> 00:58:42,818
A buffoon.

521
00:58:45,288 --> 00:58:46,778
Zorro did what was needed.

522
00:58:47,090 --> 00:58:48,730
And now he's needed again.

523
00:58:51,428 --> 00:58:53,598
I didn't ask for your help
in the cantina.

524
00:58:53,997 --> 00:58:57,716
But I came here to learn
how to fight like you.

525
00:58:58,301 --> 00:59:00,321
To have your strength, your courage.

526
00:59:01,838 --> 00:59:04,528
Now when I try to use them,
you slap me down?

527
00:59:06,376 --> 00:59:07,636
Let me tell you something...

528
00:59:07,878 --> 00:59:11,278
1 am tired of all your training,
your lecturing.

529
00:59:11,815 --> 00:59:15,475
lam tired of waiting for you
to tell me I am ready.

530
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:19,350
I have my own scores to settle.

531
00:59:19,756 --> 00:59:22,006
A new life to find.

532
00:59:23,760 --> 00:59:26,130
I thought I could do it here...

533
00:59:26,563 --> 00:59:28,053
but I was wrong.

534
00:59:29,466 --> 00:59:30,756
Alejandro!

535
00:59:32,202 --> 00:59:33,902
En garde!

536
00:59:38,175 --> 00:59:40,075
Choose your weapon.

537
00:59:59,796 --> 01:00:01,546
Montero has invited
every don in California

538
01:00:01,898 --> 01:00:04,118
to a banquet at his hacienda.

539
01:00:04,935 --> 01:00:08,335
If you want to be of service
