beyond your reach.

544
01:00:22,652 --> 01:00:24,932
Oh, yes? And what is that?

545
01:00:25,489 --> 01:00:26,979
Charm.

546
01:00:29,126 --> 01:00:30,796
And what is that?

547
01:00:34,664 --> 01:00:37,384
Convince Montero
that you're a gentleman of stature,

548
01:00:37,868 --> 01:00:40,008
and he will let you into his circle.

549
01:00:44,207 --> 01:00:45,467
Me?

550
01:00:47,077 --> 01:00:48,807
Agentleman?

551
01:00:51,381 --> 01:00:53,250
This is going to take a lot of work.

552
01:00:55,352 --> 01:00:56,612
Yes.

553
01:01:15,572 --> 01:01:16,802
Look at me.

554
01:01:17,040 --> 01:01:18,500
look like a butterfly.

555
01:01:18,808 --> 01:01:20,828
This is the most stupid thing
I've ever done.

556
01:01:21,178 --> 01:01:22,228
1 doubt that.

557
01:01:22,479 --> 01:01:25,198
-We'll never get away with this.
-Yes, we will.

558
01:01:25,815 --> 01:01:27,745
Anobleman is nothing but a man

559
01:01:28,118 --> 01:01:30,638
who says one thing
and thinks another.

560
01:01:31,054 --> 01:01:33,074
What if Montero realizes
who you are?

561
01:01:33,423 --> 01:01:36,033
Montero thinks of himself
as a true nobleman.

562
01:01:36,459 --> 01:01:38,948
He will never look
a servant in the eye.

563
01:01:39,462 --> 01:01:40,892
Listen to me.

564
01:01:41,264 --> 01:01:42,994
Listen to me!

565
01:01:45,902 --> 01:01:47,682
The most important thing of all...

566
01:01:48,038 --> 01:01:50,668
Do not let the dons leave
the table without you.

567
01:01:51,141 --> 01:01:52,071
Yes.

568
01:01:52,309 --> 01:01:53,649
Good.

569
01:01:54,110 --> 01:01:55,920
And good luck tonight.

570
01:01:56,713 --> 01:01:58,053
Thank you.

571
01:01:58,448 --> 01:02:00,317
Stand up straight.

572
01:02:00,850 --> 01:02:02,160
Charm.

573
01:02:02,919 --> 01:02:04,589
Charm.

574
01:02:22,505 --> 01:02:24,115
Don Rafael Montero?

575
01:02:24,841 --> 01:02:26,131
Good evening.

576
01:02:26,610 --> 01:02:29,300
lam Don Alejandro
del Castillo y Garcia.

577
01:02:30,180 --> 01:02:31,640
The formal greeting
of the Spanish court.

578
01:02:31,948 --> 01:02:33,758
I have not seen that in years.

579
01:02:34,818 --> 01:02:37,448
My father was very strict
in matters of etiquette.

580
01:02:37,921 --> 01:02:39,211
And who is your father?

581
01:02:39,489 --> 01:02:41,299
Don Bartolo del Castillo.

582
01:02:42,525 --> 01:02:43,485
I have heard of Don Bartolo,

583
01:02:43,727 --> 01:02:45,866
but I've never had the pleasure
of meeting him.

584
01:02:46,896 --> 01:02:49,556
l arrived last week from Spain,
by way of Paris,

585
01:02:50,033 --> 01:02:51,462
Lisbon and San Francisco.

586
01:02:51,768 --> 01:02:54,138
lam inspecting my family's holdings.

587
01:03:00,076 --> 01:03:01,886
Queen Isabella of Spain has been...

588
01:03:02,245 --> 01:03:04,234
very generous to us.

589
01:03:05,815 --> 01:03:07,655
Very impressive.

590
01:03:08,018 --> 01:03:09,628
What brings you to my door?

591
01:03:09,986 --> 01:03:11,446
When I heard you were back
in California,

592
01:03:11,755 --> 01:03:13,925
I knew I...must introduce myself.

593
01:03:14,324 --> 01:03:16,814
Her Royal Highness speaks
very highly of you.

594
01:03:19,162 --> 01:03:20,392
Really?

595
01:03:21,231 --> 01:03:22,281
I was under the impression

596
01:03:22,532 --> 01:03:23,992
I was out of favor
with the Spanish court

597
01:03:24,301 --> 01:03:26,761
since alifornia was lost to Mexico.

598
01:03:32,909 --> 01:03:35,099
Only in certain circles.

599
01:03:35,578 --> 01:03:36,338
Her Majesty knows

600
01:03:36,513 --> 01:03:39,883
those unfortunate events were clearly
no fault of yours.

601
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:42,683
She also told me this province

602
01:03:42,919 --> 01:03:45,669
is still a land of opportunity
for a man of vision.

603
01:03:46,623 --> 01:03:48,403
And you are a man of vision?

604
01:03:49,392 --> 01:03:52,962
lam a man...in search of a vision.

605
01:03:55,498 --> 01:03:57,608
But my timing is unfortunate.

606
01:03:57,967 --> 01:03:59,697
[ have interrupted a party.

607
01:04:00,003 --> 01:04:02,113
Perhaps I could call again.

608
01:04:03,673 --> 01:04:06,982
No, no, it would,
honor me for you to join us.

609
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:09,970
It would honor me to do so, sir.

610
01:04:10,580 --> 01:04:13,190
Please, allow me tointroduce
my daughter...Elena.

611
01:04:13,616 --> 01:04:14,926
Of course.

612
01:04:18,588 --> 01:04:19,958
Charmed.

613
01:04:23,793 --> 01:04:26,983
I'm afraid I have brought no gift
for the hostess.

614
01:04:27,597 --> 01:04:30,697
But...wait a moment.

615
01:04:42,445 --> 01:04:43,295
Thank you.

616
01:04:43,513 --> 01:04:45,123
My pleasure.

617
01:04:49,586 --> 01:04:51,836
Bernardo...pick up your feet.

618
01:04:52,255 --> 01:04:53,565
Senorita.

619
01:04:53,857 --> 01:04:55,087
Caballero.

620
01:05:20,216 --> 01:05:21,915
Don Alejandro.

621
01:05:23,620 --> 01:05:26,549
My father and I would like you
to join us at our table.

622
01:05:27,223 --> 01:05:29,683
I would be delighted, senorita.

623
01:05:42,806 --> 01:05:45,616
Don Alejandro,
I'm so pleased you could join us.

624
01:05:46,109 --> 01:05:46,869
Gentlemen, allow me

625
01:05:47,043 --> 01:05:49,503
to introduce Don Alejandro
del Castillo y Garcia,

626
01:05:49,913 --> 01:05:51,843
recently returned from Spain.

627
01:05:52,215 --> 01:05:55,115
This is, Captain Harrison Love.

628
01:05:55,585 --> 01:05:58,215
Not a don, but...
certainly a kindred spirit.

629
01:06:00,323 --> 01:06:01,223
Are you not the man

630
01:06:01,458 --> 01:06:04,178
who was chasing
a legendary bandit recently?

631
01:06:05,228 --> 01:06:06,568
He was hardly legendary.

632
01:06:06,863 --> 01:06:07,763
So you caught him?

633
01:06:08,798 --> 01:06:11,017
It's only a matter of time.

634
01:06:12,268 --> 01:06:14,788
Well, the bandit may have escaped,

635
01:06:15,205 --> 01:06:17,455
but the rest of us
will certainly think twice

636
01:06:17,874 --> 01:06:19,604
before going to confession.

637
01:06:43,967 --> 01:06:45,257
Thank you.

638
01:06:48,705 --> 01:06:51,285
With all due respect, Don Hector,
I disagree.

639
01:06:52,075 --> 01:06:54,245
Until these people are free to...
govern themselves,

640
01:06:54,644 --> 01:06:57,953
I think we will see many more "Z's
carved into walls.

641
01:06:59,916 --> 01:07:02,026
Don Alejandro, what do you think?

642
01:07:04,187 --> 01:07:08,727
I think...the sheep
will always need a shepherd.

643
01:07:09,459 --> 01:07:13,848
But, certainly not this...
Zorro creature.

644
01:07:14,564 --> 01:07:16,053
He probably wears the mask

645
01:07:16,366 --> 01:07:19,266
to hide his bald head
and unsightly features.

646
01:07:23,206 --> 01:07:25,396
There are some
who would call him heroic.

647
01:07:25,808 --> 01:07:28,028
Heroism. A romantic illusion.

648
01:07:28,444 --> 01:07:30,634
-Much like nobility?
-Elena, that is enough.

649
01:07:31,814 --> 01:07:33,074
Myself, I would think heroism is...

650
01:07:33,316 --> 01:07:35,566
something to aspire to, not sneer at.

651
01:07:35,985 --> 01:07:37,275
All that playing with swords...

652
01:07:37,520 --> 01:07:40,130
shooting guns,
racing around with horses.

653
01:07:40,590 --> 01:07:42,580
Gives me a frightful headache.

654
01:07:43,226 --> 01:07:46,156
Such sweaty pursuits are...
hardly the work of a gentleman.

655
01:07:46,629 --> 01:07:47,558
And what is?

656
01:07:47,797 --> 01:07:49,497
Climbing in and out of carriages?

657
01:07:49,799 --> 01:07:51,199
No, my dear.

658
01:07:51,734 --> 01:07:53,024
But increasing one's holdings

659
01:07:53,303 --> 01:07:56,373
so as to provide lavish
comfort for ladies...

660
01:07:57,340 --> 01:07:59,390
such as yourself.

661
01:08:06,049 --> 01:08:08,659
A woman's grasp of politics.
What can I say?

662
01:08:12,622 --> 01:08:14,432
Well, we're at a party, aren't we?

663
01:08:14,791 --> 01:08:18,041
Elena...may I have the honor
of this dance?

664
01:08:21,698 --> 01:08:23,218
