665
01:09:11,413 --> 01:09:12,703
Yes?

666
01:09:13,015 --> 01:09:14,656
Were you looking for something?

667
01:09:14,951 --> 01:09:18,081
Asense of the miraculous
in everyday life.

668
01:09:19,087 --> 01:09:19,957
Oh, really?

669
01:09:20,189 --> 01:09:22,119
Well, why don't you try
looking someplace else?

670
01:09:22,492 --> 01:09:24,221
The lady and ! were trying to dance.

671
01:09:24,560 --> 01:09:26,230
You were trying.

672
01:09:26,763 --> 01:09:28,403
She was succeeding.

673
01:09:30,033 --> 01:09:33,843
Forgive me, Capitan,
a shameless joke at your expense.

674
01:09:34,437 --> 01:09:36,216
And I hope it will not be the last.

675
01:09:36,572 --> 01:09:38,502
Don Rafael wants you back
at his table...

676
01:09:39,809 --> 01:09:41,038
Pino.

677
01:10:26,923 --> 01:10:29,532
Would you care to try
something more, robust?

678
01:10:29,992 --> 01:10:31,452
Or do you feel unequal to the task?

679
01:10:31,761 --> 01:10:33,871
No, on the contrary, Don Alejandro.

680
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:37,629
I think only of your distaste
for perspiration.

681
01:10:39,235 --> 01:10:41,105
-Maestro...
-Si.

682
01:12:07,123 --> 01:12:10,723
Well, If that's the way they are
dancing in Madrid these days...

683
01:12:11,327 --> 01:12:13,877
Excuse me, Don Rafael.
I need to catch my breath.

684
01:12:14,297 --> 01:12:16,666
Your daughter
is a very spirited dancer.

685
01:12:17,567 --> 01:12:18,877
"Spirited."

686
01:12:19,168 --> 01:12:21,628
Thank you for putting it so delicately.

687
01:12:26,742 --> 01:12:28,472
l apologize if you were offended.

688
01:12:28,778 --> 01:12:32,178
Oh, no. Completely unnecessary,
l assure you.

689
01:12:32,715 --> 01:12:34,355
She's and impulsive...

690
01:12:34,650 --> 01:12:36,610
but her beauty is beyond compare.

691
01:12:36,986 --> 01:12:40,296
And she has her father's
commanding presence.

692
01:12:42,592 --> 01:12:44,112
Don Rafael?

693
01:12:48,064 --> 01:12:50,114
As...an advisor
to Her Royal Highness

694
01:12:50,466 --> 01:12:51,956
in matters of finance...

695
01:12:52,702 --> 01:12:56,512
it would be my pleasure
to introduce you both at court.

696
01:13:06,949 --> 01:13:08,029
Join us in the courtyard.

697
01:13:08,284 --> 01:13:10,454
There's something
I would like to share with you.

698
01:13:11,120 --> 01:13:12,550
What is that?

699
01:13:12,889 --> 01:13:14,529
Avision.

700
01:13:24,634 --> 01:13:26,914
Fellow dons of California...

701
01:13:27,703 --> 01:13:29,843
all of us here can recall
the golden years

702
01:13:30,206 --> 01:13:31,816
when we ruled this country.

703
01:13:32,441 --> 01:13:34,251
We commanded respect
as noblemen

704
01:13:34,610 --> 01:13:36,920
and we amassed
a great deal of wealth.

705
01:13:37,346 --> 01:13:39,486
There was something that
we never achieved.

706
01:13:39,949 --> 01:13:43,869
We never determined our own...
destiny.

707
01:13:44,620 --> 01:13:47,140
Well...the time has come.

708
01:13:47,556 --> 01:13:50,545
Time to claim what always
should have been ours.

709
01:13:51,427 --> 01:13:52,826
My friends...

710
01:13:54,096 --> 01:13:55,356
I give...you...

711
01:13:55,598 --> 01:13:59,577
the independent Republic
of California.

712
01:14:15,184 --> 01:14:16,824
Don Rafael...

713
01:14:17,119 --> 01:14:19,049
every man here owes
you something.

714
01:14:19,422 --> 01:14:21,911
The land you gave us
made us all wealthy men.

715
01:14:22,325 --> 01:14:25,894
However,
we must question your motives.

716
01:14:26,896 --> 01:14:29,996
The day you arrived on the beach
you made us all look like fools.

717
01:14:30,533 --> 01:14:31,873
That is absurd, Don Pedro.

718
01:14:32,168 --> 01:14:33,478
I was merely playing to the crowd.

719
01:14:33,769 --> 01:14:36,729
And what are you doing now,
if not playing to the crowd?

720
01:14:37,440 --> 01:14:40,980
Now you're inciting us
to raise arms against Santa Anna,

721
01:14:41,577 --> 01:14:44,477
when you know perfectly well
we could never defeat his army.

722
01:14:44,947 --> 01:14:47,987
I was not suggesting that
we fight him for California.

723
01:14:48,584 --> 01:14:51,514
I was suggesting that we buy it...
from him.

724
01:14:52,488 --> 01:14:54,218
Santa Anna is waging
.
a very ex...pensive war

725
01:14:54,523 --> 01:14:57,513
with the United States
increasingly short of money.

726
01:14:57,994 --> 01:15:00,544
Even if we all...
and is combined our fortunes,

727
01:15:00,963 --> 01:15:02,223
we could not come up
with enough money

728
01:15:02,465 --> 01:15:04,715
to buy this country from Santa Anna.

729
01:15:05,134 --> 01:15:07,444
I have already
brokered a deal with him.

730
01:15:08,838 --> 01:15:10,888
You're living in a dream, Montero.

731
01:15:12,842 --> 01:15:15,831
Then why don't we all live
in the same dream together?

732
01:15:31,827 --> 01:15:33,607
Meet me here tomorrow morning,
gentlemen,

733
01:15:33,963 --> 01:15:35,333
for a journey that will open your eyes

734
01:15:35,631 --> 01:15:38,031
and lay all your doubts to rest.

735
01:16:31,353 --> 01:16:33,463
My friends, I give you...

736
01:16:35,157 --> 01:16:36,357
El Dorado.

737
01:16:46,869 --> 01:16:49,679
Technically, of course,
all this gold be...longs to Santa Anna.

738
01:16:50,172 --> 01:16:51,102
But fortunately for us,

739
01:16:51,340 --> 01:16:53,950
he's completely
unaware of its existence.

740
01:16:54,610 --> 01:16:55,630
Now, for the deception to work,

741
01:16:55,878 --> 01:16:58,428
all these bars have been marked
with the Spanish seal,

742
01:16:58,848 --> 01:17:01,038
so that he will think
they have come from Spain.

743
01:17:02,118 --> 01:17:04,638
You see now, gentlemen?
Is it becoming clearer to you?

744
01:17:05,588 --> 01:17:06,438
Two days from now,

745
01:17:06,655 --> 01:17:09,315
we will buy this country
from Santa Anna.

746
01:17:09,859 --> 01:17:12,989
And we...will buy it with gold dug
from his own land.

747
01:17:24,006 --> 01:17:25,846
Where did you find these people?

748
01:17:27,176 --> 01:17:28,786
Anywhere we wanted.

749
01:17:30,212 --> 01:17:31,552
Brilliant.

750
01:17:33,516 --> 01:17:34,856
Brilliant.

751
01:17:38,154 --> 01:17:40,204
It's only part of the mining process.

752
01:17:40,856 --> 01:17:42,465
First, we were just picking it up
off the ground,

753
01:17:42,758 --> 01:17:44,428
but now we're down to blasting.

754
01:17:58,974 --> 01:18:02,604
So...is this the future of California?

755
01:18:04,380 --> 01:18:06,570
This is my vision, yes.

756
01:18:09,618 --> 01:18:11,928
Basura, up here!

757
01:18:12,354 --> 01:18:16,044
Well, now ain't you a sight
for sore eyes!

758
01:18:16,825 --> 01:18:21,135
Full-growed vultures walkin’ around
like real folk.

759
01:18:21,797 --> 01:18:22,817
Welcome!

760
01:18:23,065 --> 01:18:25,554
Welcome to hell's outhouse.

761
01:18:26,402 --> 01:18:28,622
Now, they call us
the disappeared ones.

762
01:18:29,038 --> 01:18:32,027
But as you can...see,
we ain't exactly disappeared.

763
01:18:32,508 --> 01:18:34,237
We just been a little hard to find.

764
01:18:34,543 --> 01:18:35,272
Wait!

765
01:18:35,444 --> 01:18:37,664
You! I know you.

766
01:18:38,080 --> 01:18:39,750
You bet you do, peckerwood!

767
01:18:40,049 --> 01:18:42,329
I'm the legendary
Three-Fingered Jack!

768
01:18:42,751 --> 01:18:45,941
And you...
are a bunch of murderin' trash...

769
01:18:46,488 --> 01:18:50,408
dressed up in fancy,
sweet-smellin' doodads.

770
01:18:51,060 --> 01:18:53,810
Ignore him, gentlemen.
He's a common thief.

771
01:18:54,830 --> 01:18:56,500
As common as they come.

772
01:18:56,799 --> 01:19:00,369
But I ain't nothin’
compared to you gentlemen.

773
01:19:00,970 --> 01:19:03,520
I steal gold. ! steal...money.

774
01:19:03,939 --> 01:19:07,949
But you...you steal people's lives.

775
01:19:08,611 --> 01:19:09,601
So damn you...

776
01:19:09,845 --> 01:19:12,095
and damn the horse that brung you!

777
01:19:32,034 --> 01:19:33,433
Peckerwood?

778
01:20:16,011 --> 01:20:19,201
Is there something...
amusing, Captain?

779
01:20:20,416 --> 01:20:21,966
Strange, I'd say.

780
01:20:23,319 --> 01:20:24,579
It's the second time
l've shot this man

781
01:20:24,820 --> 01:20:26,780
while he was flying through the air.

782
01:20:35,297 --> 01:20:36,906
Don Alejandro!

783
01:20:37,933 --> 01:20:40,303
I need to speak with you
at the hacienda. Alone.

784
01:20:41,570 --> 01:20:43,650
Some other time. Perhaps.

785
01:20:44,006 --> 01:20:46,616
Today. Alone.

786
01:21:09,932 --> 01:21:11,922
Good afternoon, Bernardo.

787
01:21:13,969 --> 01:21:15,779
Good afternoon, senorita.

788
01:21:16,338 --> 01:21:18,508
Your voice is so calming.

789
01:21:19,007 --> 01:21:21,376
He's high-spirited.
He needs to hear something soothing.

790
01:21:21,810 --> 01:21:23,510
Yes, l understand.

791
01:21:26,348 --> 01:21:29,008
How long have you served
Don Alejandro?

792
01:21:29,485 --> 01:21:31,674
Sometimes it seems interminable.

793
01:21:32,087 --> 01:21:33,457
I'm sorry, l speak out of place.

794
01:21:33,756 --> 01:21:34,806
Do not worry, Bernardo.

795
01:21:35,057 --> 01:21:36,867
He will not hear it from me.

796
01:21:39,061 --> 01:21:41,901
Don Alejandro confuses me.

797
01:21:43,098 --> 01:21:47,458
Sometimes he seems
so arrogant, so superior.

798
01:21:48,871 --> 01:21:50,861
And yet, the way
that he looks at me and...

799
01:21:51,240 --> 01:21:53,960
the way that he dances with me...

800
01:21:54,543 --> 01:21:57,173
as if he were two completely
different men.

801
01:22:07,289 --> 01:22:09,309
You look so much like your mother.

802
01:22:12,294 --> 01:22:13,724
How would you know that?

803
01:22:14,029 --> 01:22:19,709
Well...l don't see much
of Don Rafael in you.

804
01:22:22,137 --> 01:22:24,887
I know my father wishes
l acted more like her.

805
01:22:25,374 --> 01:22:28,834
She was very proper...
my mother, always appropriate.

806
01:22:29,411 --> 01:22:30,961
Is that how he describes her?

807
01:22:31,280 --> 01:22:34,269
Yes, but sometimes
I do not believe him.

808
01:22:34,983 --> 01:22:36,153
She was more like you.

809
01:22:38,454 --> 01:22:39,943
Perhaps.

810
01:22:40,823 --> 01:22:42,693
It would be a way of knowing her.

811
01:22:46,762 --> 01:22:48,602
My ninera once told me

812
01:22:48,964 --> 01:22:51,484
that the departed can see you
in the moonlight.

813
01:22:52,267 --> 01:22:53,117
So when I was young,

814
01:22:53,335 --> 01:22:55,005
l used to sneak
out of my window at night

815
01:22:55,304 --> 01:22:58,084
and ride my horse across Andalusia.

816
01:22:58,974 --> 01:23:02,044
And would wave at the sky,
so she would know it was me.

817
01:23:08,183 --> 01:23:09,523
How did she die?

818
01:23:09,818 --> 01:23:11,218
Giving birth to me.

819
01:23:14,089 --> 01:23:17,189
My father rarely speaks of her.
I think he finds it too painful.

820
01:23:19,328 --> 01:23:20,998
Yes.

821
01:23:27,469 --> 01:23:29,369
I know what it is like to lose a...

822
01:23:29,738 --> 01:23:30,968
a loved one.

823
01:23:31,240 --> 01:23:32,469
You?

824
01:23:34,009 --> 01:23:37,789
Yeah, a daughter...long ago.

825
01:23:40,282 --> 01:23:42,302
When I see you, I remember what it...

826
01:23:42,651 --> 01:23:44,760
felt like to be a father.

827
01:23:49,057 --> 01:23:51,987
I'm sure your mother would be
very proud of you, senorita.

828
01:23:52,794 --> 01:23:54,464
Thank you,

829
01:23:57,533 --> 01:24:01,343
Bernardo. I have to ask you...
have we ever met before?

830
01:24:02,271 --> 01:24:04,931
No. Why would you think that?

831
01:24:06,542 --> 01:24:08,972
I do not know. It's strange.

832
01:24:09,478 --> 01:24:12,088
Your voice seems so familiar,
somehow.

833
01:24:12,781 --> 01:24:15,821
But haven't been to Spain
since before you were born.

834
01:24:17,386 --> 01:24:18,726
Of course.

835
01:24:21,056 --> 01:24:23,396
Well, it's a very pleasant voice.

836
01:24:25,327 --> 01:24:26,757
Thank you.

837
01:24:27,829 --> 01:24:29,228
Good day, Bernardo.

838
01:24:29,531 --> 01:24:30,961
Good day...

839
01:24:36,939 --> 01:24:38,749
Elena.

840
01:24:53,789 --> 01:24:57,188
Did you know that the Compa Indians
of central Peru used to...

841
01:24:57,726 --> 01:25:01,186
cannibalize their slain enemies
in order to absorb their power?

842
01:25:02,464 --> 01:25:05,484
The eyes, in particular,
were most sought after.

843
01:25:08,904 --> 01:25:11,244
To be able to see
through the eyes of an enemy...

844
01:25:12,541 --> 01:25:14,411
is a valuable thing.

845
01:25:19,648 --> 01:25:20,578
Where are my manners?

846
01:25:20,816 --> 01:25:24,356
Would you...Would you care
for something to drink?

847
01:25:30,759 --> 01:25:31,929
No?

848
01:25:32,928 --> 01:25:35,508
A different vintage, perhaps?

849
01:25:44,873 --> 01:25:47,183
You're a very sick person,
Capitan Love.

850
01:25:49,144 --> 01:25:52,394
Heads in water jars,
hands in wine pitchers must,

851
01:25:52,948 --> 01:25:55,138
... Strike you as odd. ] suppose.

852
01:25:57,052 --> 01:25:58,661
Well, for one thing...

853
01:25:58,954 --> 01:26:01,174
I think you ought
to fire your housekeeper.

854
01:26:07,295 --> 01:26:08,585
Who is he?

855
01:26:09,564 --> 01:26:10,904
An enemy.

856
01:26:13,068 --> 01:26:15,998
He has a brother out there
who will share the same fate.

857
01:26:19,441 --> 01:26:20,961
I wish you luck.

858
01:26:26,181 --> 01:26:26,731
To your health.

859
01:26:26,915 --> 01:26:28,995
Murrieta's brother or not...

860
01:26:30,185 --> 01:26:32,235
you are more than
you pretend to be.

861
01:26:33,555 --> 01:26:35,225
Maybe someday...

862
01:26:35,524 --> 01:26:37,954
! will see what ! look like
through your eyes...

863
01:26:38,393 --> 01:26:40,263
Capitan Love.

864
01:27:26,608 --> 01:27:28,508
Oh, it is beautiful.

865
01:27:44,826 --> 01:27:47,016
Excuse me...how much does it cost?

866
01:27:53,969 --> 01:27:57,449
It is a gift, she says...
in honor of your mother.

867
01:27:59,107 --> 01:28:00,397
My mother?

868
01:28:01,843 --> 01:28:03,923
She loved your mother.

869
01:28:04,613 --> 01:28:06,313
No, tell her she must be mistaken.

870
01:28:06,615 --> 01:28:08,835
My mother died long ago in Spain.

871
01:28:20,996 --> 01:28:22,546
She says there's no mistaking

872
01:28:22,831 --> 01:28:25,701
the daughter of Esperanza
and Diego de la Vega.

873
01:28:26,268 --> 01:28:28,408
She says she was your nanny.

874
01:28:28,804 --> 01:28:31,614
She hung flowers on your crib
when you were little.

875
01:28:35,110 --> 01:28:37,540
I'm sorry, l cannot accept it.

876
01:28:56,998 --> 01:28:58,548
Alejandro?

877
01:29:00,135 --> 01:29:01,945
Alejandro, listen to me.

878
01:29:02,537 --> 01:29:04,877
Can you find your way back
to the mine?

879
01:29:06,908 --> 01:29:08,248
No.

880
01:29:09,744 --> 01:29:12,464
The carriage windows
were all covered.

881
01:29:14,049 --> 01:29:15,749
He didn't even trust his own dons.

882
01:29:16,051 --> 01:29:17,801
Nor would I.

883
01:29:18,153 --> 01:29:20,023
You must go to Montero's house
tonight.

884
01:29:20,522 --> 01:29:22,332
Break into the chest in his study.

885
01:29:22,657 --> 01:29:24,357
Find anything that will tell us
what his plans are...

886
01:29:24,659 --> 01:29:26,799
People in the mine are dying...

887
01:29:27,896 --> 01:29:30,936
and...all 1 can think of is...

888
01:29:31,833 --> 01:29:33,263
Capitan Love.

889
01:29:33,535 --> 01:29:34,764
He will come into your circle
soon enough.

890
01:29:35,003 --> 01:29:36,702
You need not chase him.

891
01:29:40,008 --> 01:29:42,468
-[ miss my brother, sir.
-Your brother is dead!

892
01:29:43,311 --> 01:29:44,331
We lose the ones we love.

893
01:29:44,546 --> 01:29:46,506
We cannot change it. Put it aside.

894
01:29:47,349 --> 01:29:48,659
How?

895
01:29:50,719 --> 01:29:56,869
How can I do what is needed,
when all I feel is...hate?

896
01:29:59,527 --> 01:30:00,957
You hide it...

897
01:30:03,131 --> 01:30:04,651
with this.

898
01:30:16,244 --> 01:30:18,114
Santa Anna has agreed
to the transfer at noon,

899
01:30:18,446 --> 01:30:19,526
the day after tomorrow.

900
01:30:19,748 --> 01:30:22,678
But he insists we deliver the gold
five miles north of town.

901
01:30:23,151 --> 01:30:24,291
Captain Love?

902
01:30:28,356 --> 01:30:29,465
I's a safe distance from the mine.

903
01:30:29,691 --> 01:30:31,391
The bars are stamped and ready.

904
01:30:31,693 --> 01:30:33,533
I don't foresee a problem.

905
01:30:34,229 --> 01:30:35,659
Tell him we agree.

906
01:30:36,097 --> 01:30:38,437
You've done well, Luiz, very well.

907
01:30:42,637 --> 01:30:45,507
To the independent
Republic of California.

908
01:30:49,778 --> 01:30:51,768
Don Rafael!

909
01:31:16,871 --> 01:31:19,241
Did you send men to the hills?
Double the guard at the wall?

910
01:31:19,641 --> 01:31:21,130
Yes, yes, of course.

911
01:31:27,749 --> 01:31:29,329
After all, it's only one man.

912
01:31:29,617 --> 01:31:32,077
It isn't just one man, damn it!
It's Zorro.

913
01:31:34,122 --> 01:31:35,642
And he knows about the mine.

914
01:31:35,924 --> 01:31:38,114
Otherwise he wouldn't be here tonight.

915
01:31:39,294 --> 01:31:41,544
-How could he possibly...
-It doesn't matter how.

916
01:31:42,664 --> 01:31:44,534
You don't seem to grasp the...
situation, Captain.

917
01:31:44,866 --> 01:31:45,856
lf Santa Anna...finds out

918
01:31:46,067 --> 01:31:47,767
that we have paid him in gold stolen
from his own land,

919
01:31:48,069 --> 01:31:50,059
he will have us butchered like cattle.

920
01:31:50,405 --> 01:31:52,014
Do you understand?

921
01:31:54,843 --> 01:31:56,923
Then we should destroy the evidence.

922
01:31:57,379 --> 01:31:59,779
Set explosives, bury the mine.

923
01:32:01,750 --> 01:32:02,620
And the workers?

924
01:32:02,817 --> 01:32:05,157
We destroy all the evidence,
Don Rafael.

925
01:32:05,553 --> 01:32:07,043
No witnesses.

926
01:32:14,262 --> 01:32:16,192
Make sure those papers
are locked up.

927
01:32:34,716 --> 01:32:35,856
Guards!

928
01:32:45,293 --> 01:32:47,043
The much-debated Zorro.

929
01:32:47,362 --> 01:32:48,562
No.

930
01:32:49,264 --> 01:32:51,104
The legendary Zorro.

931
01:32:53,902 --> 01:32:54,982
Put down your weapons!

932
01:32:56,237 --> 01:32:57,467
Tell them.

933
01:32:57,906 --> 01:32:59,426
Do as he says!

934
01:33:06,147 --> 01:33:07,457
Allow me.

935
01:33:14,355 --> 01:33:15,554
Come.

936
01:33:16,324 --> 01:33:17,584
Stop.

937
01:33:18,493 --> 01:33:20,163
Face the window.

938
01:33:21,596 --> 01:33:25,056
Now...bend down
and touch your toes.

939
01:33:27,502 --> 01:33:29,402
Bend over.

940
01:33:31,639 --> 01:33:33,539
Would you excuse me, Capitan Love?

941
01:33:35,143 --> 01:33:36,453
Thank you.

942
01:34:53,087 --> 01:34:54,197
Alto!

943
01:35:59,954 --> 01:36:00,974
Kill him.

944
01:36:30,318 --> 01:36:31,748
Good morning, senor.

945
01:36:36,691 --> 01:36:37,951
Good morning, senorita.

946
01:36:38,192 --> 01:36:39,482
Give it back.

947
01:36:39,961 --> 01:36:40,511
What?

948
01:36:40,662 --> 01:36:42,942
Whatever it is you have stolen
from my father.

949
01:36:43,331 --> 01:36:45,231
] want it back. Give it to me.

950
01:36:46,567 --> 01:36:47,967
No.

951
01:36:55,176 --> 01:36:56,346
Come on, now.

952
01:37:10,892 --> 01:37:13,581
I don't have the time to give you
the proper instruction.

953
01:37:16,264 --> 01:37:19,304
I have had the proper instruction
since I was four.

954
01:38:13,621 --> 01:38:14,851
Not bad.

955
01:38:17,859 --> 01:38:19,199
Not bad at all.

956
01:38:42,417 --> 01:38:44,167
This will make it more difficult,

957
01:38:46,020 --> 01:38:47,450
senori...ta.

958
01:39:12,380 --> 01:39:13,550
Don't move.

959
01:39:34,769 --> 01:39:36,289
Do you surrender?

960
01:39:36,671 --> 01:39:38,401
Never.

961
01:39:39,240 --> 01:39:41,290
But l may scream.

962
01:39:42,643 --> 01:39:44,423
l understand.

963
01:39:44,912 --> 01:39:47,102
Sometimes I have that effect.

964
01:40:16,310 --> 01:40:17,390
Excuse me.

965
01:40:21,115 --> 01:40:22,695
Goodbye, senorita.

966
01:40:35,162 --> 01:40:36,802
What are you doing here?
What happened?

967
01:40:37,098 --> 01:40:38,298
Zorro.

968
01:40:38,533 --> 01:40:41,143
Zorro was here.
I fought him, and he left.

969
01:40:41,569 --> 01:40:42,589
He left!

970
01:40:42,803 --> 01:40:44,032
Do you recognize him?

971
01:40:44,272 --> 01:40:48,312
No. But he was and vigorous.

972
01:40:49,443 --> 01:40:51,583
He was very vigorous, Father.

973
01:40:52,547 --> 01:40:53,776
Vigorous?

974
01:40:54,015 --> 01:40:55,415
Yes.

975
01:41:34,789 --> 01:41:36,018
Let's go!

976
01:42:53,501 --> 01:42:54,321
Go!

977
01:43:32,640 --> 01:43:33,510
Come on!

978
01:44:08,542 --> 01:44:10,972
Here...this is the canyon.

979
01:44:11,378 --> 01:44:13,048
That is where the mine is.

980
01:44:14,615 --> 01:44:18,594
They have...twenty five,
thirty guards at most.

981
01:44:19,453 --> 01:44:20,683
Nothing that Zorro can't overcome.

982
01:44:20,921 --> 01:44:22,501
I'm not going with you.

983
01:44:22,790 --> 01:44:24,130
What?

984
01:44:25,226 --> 01:44:27,036
I'm not going with you.

985
01:44:28,929 --> 01:44:32,179
There's something I must do.
It's a personal matter.

986
01:44:34,168 --> 01:44:35,628
What about the prisoners?

987
01:44:35,903 --> 01:44:37,743
There's nothing more
I can do for them.

988
01:44:39,340 --> 01:44:40,710
You mean, nothing you will do.

989
01:44:40,975 --> 01:44:42,755
I gave my life to them!

990
01:44:44,078 --> 01:44:45,978
And in return, I lost everything.

991
01:44:46,313 --> 01:44:47,713
My wife was murdered
before my eyes

992
01:44:47,982 --> 01:44:51,852
and my child was stolen to be raised
by my mortal enemy.

993
01:44:52,653 --> 01:44:54,233
Montero?

994
01:44:57,491 --> 01:44:59,041
Elena.

995
01:45:01,228 --> 01:45:02,838
She's your daughter.

996
01:45:04,565 --> 01:45:06,235
Yes, she was.

997
01:45:10,971 --> 01:45:12,311
So...

998
01:45:13,741 --> 01:45:15,411
you will simply take your revenge.

999
01:45:15,709 --> 01:45:17,729
No. ! will take my daughter.

1000
01:45:18,078 --> 01:45:19,948
And don't pretend
she means nothing to you.

1001
01:45:20,281 --> 01:45:21,651
Well, she does.

1002
01:45:21,916 --> 01:45:24,986
But you taught me to see
beyond personal feelings, remember?

1003
01:45:25,486 --> 01:45:27,326
Was that all a lie?

1004
01:45:28,856 --> 01:45:31,846
-You're too to understand.
-To understand what?

1005
01:45:32,526 --> 01:45:34,135
Betrayal?

1006
01:45:34,562 --> 01:45:36,732
All the work, all the training,
all the wise words.

1007
01:45:37,097 --> 01:45:38,387
For what?

1008
01:45:38,632 --> 01:45:40,562
To smile in the face
of my brother's killer,

1009
01:45:40,901 --> 01:45:42,800
while you make your own plans?

1010
01:45:46,674 --> 01:45:49,664
Alejandro, I taught you
everything you need to survive.

1011
01:45:50,978 --> 01:45:52,648
Now I must look to my own heart.

1012
01:45:55,216 --> 01:45:57,026
Elena is all have left.

1013
01:45:57,351 --> 01:45:58,960
I'm not going to lose her again.

1014
01:46:02,356 --> 01:46:03,936
What about California?

1015
01:46:04,225 --> 01:46:05,805
What about the people?

1016
01:46:06,994 --> 01:46:09,044
They still have Zorro.

1017
01:46:37,992 --> 01:46:40,072
I've every inch
of the countryside covered.

1018
01:46:40,427 --> 01:46:42,036
If he shows himself...

1019
01:46:44,498 --> 01:46:45,288
are you all right?

1020
01:46:45,466 --> 01:46:46,806
Do you have the map?

1021
01:46:47,067 --> 01:46:48,087
We'll find it.

1022
01:46:48,302 --> 01:46:50,552
Is your army ready to fight
Santa Anna's?

1023
01:46:50,938 --> 01:46:51,368
No, sir.

1024
01:46:51,505 --> 01:46:52,875
Then why are you asking me
if I'm all right?

1025
01:46:53,140 --> 01:46:54,070
Of course I'm not all right.

1026
01:46:54,275 --> 01:46:55,264
You know,
I'm really beginning to wonder

1027
01:46:55,476 --> 01:46:57,585
if you want this operation
to succeed at all. Captain Love.

1028
01:46:57,945 --> 01:46:59,085
Just what are you saying,
Don Rafael?

1029
01:46:59,313 --> 01:47:00,483
What I'm saying, Captain,

1030
01:47:00,714 --> 01:47:03,524
is that I think that my horse
could run this army better than you.

1031
01:47:09,089 --> 01:47:10,669
I said I'll find him.

1032
01:47:13,560 --> 01:47:15,080
That means I will.

1033
01:47:18,365 --> 01:47:20,175
Perhaps I can save you the trouble.

1034
01:47:20,501 --> 01:47:22,491
Go on, reach for it...Captain!

1035
01:47:24,972 --> 01:47:26,282
Who are you?

1036
01:47:26,740 --> 01:47:28,760
I warned you long ago, Rafael...

1037
01:47:30,844 --> 01:47:32,454
you would never be rid of me.

1038
01:47:33,314 --> 01:47:34,894
De la Vega.

1039
01:47:38,686 --> 01:47:39,915
Rafael.

1040
01:47:40,154 --> 01:47:42,674
You were not the Zorro
I saw last night.

1041
01:47:43,357 --> 01:47:45,347
That was your master,
Don Alejandro.

1042
01:47:45,693 --> 01:47:46,983
Yes.

1043
01:47:47,494 --> 01:47:50,714
But there are many who would
proudly wear the mask of Zorro.

1044
01:47:51,231 --> 01:47:53,101
Either way, it's of little consequence.

1045
01:47:53,434 --> 01:47:56,014
Events have been set in motion
that you cannot stop.

1046
01:47:56,637 --> 01:47:58,507
I'm not here to stop you.

1047
01:48:00,474 --> 01:48:02,374
Call for Elena.

1048
01:48:06,413 --> 01:48:07,963
Call her.

1049
01:48:10,317 --> 01:48:11,897
Captain...

1050
01:48:12,686 --> 01:48:14,646
bring my daughter to me.

1051
01:48:16,357 --> 01:48:17,667
Bring her to me!

1052
01:48:26,934 --> 01:48:29,124
You cannot imagine, Rafael,

1053
01:48:29,503 --> 01:48:31,433
how I have dreamed
of this moment.

1054
01:48:31,772 --> 01:48:35,052
Night and day, twenty long years.

1055
01:48:36,577 --> 01:48:38,007
Really?

1056
01:48:38,679 --> 01:48:40,989
[ haven't given you a second thought.

1057
01:48:41,982 --> 01:48:45,822
If l...die, De la Vega,
the truth dies with me.

1058
01:48:47,254 --> 01:48:48,364
We shall see.

1059
01:48:48,589 --> 01:48:49,818
Father!

1060
01:48:50,591 --> 01:48:52,641
Bernardo, what are you doing?

1061
01:48:52,993 --> 01:48:54,773
Tell her, Rafael.

1062
01:48:56,263 --> 01:48:58,403
Tell me what? What is going on?

1063
01:48:58,766 --> 01:49:01,375
Tell her who her real father is.

1064
01:49:02,036 --> 01:49:04,226
Father, what is he saying?

1065
01:49:06,840 --> 01:49:10,910
This...unfortunate man
lost a daughter once...

1066
01:49:11,545 --> 01:49:12,395
and it has driven him mad.

1067
01:49:12,579 --> 01:49:15,099
And...now,
he seeks to claim you for his own.

1068
01:49:17,418 --> 01:49:20,878
Tell her how her mother died.

1069
01:49:24,558 --> 01:49:27,278
Your daughter is lost, De la Vega.

1070
01:49:28,662 --> 01:49:30,242
You cannot have mine.

1071
01:49:30,531 --> 01:49:32,371
De la Vega?

1072
01:49:33,967 --> 01:49:36,626
A woman in town, she told me.

1073
01:49:38,439 --> 01:49:41,279
Diego De la Vega?

1074
01:49:43,944 --> 01:49:45,374
Father?

1075
01:49:46,647 --> 01:49:48,667
His name is of no consequence.

1076
01:49:52,920 --> 01:49:56,080
I was told my ninera used
to hang something on my crib.

1077
01:49:57,891 --> 01:50:01,290
Yes...she had her hang
a...fresh...flower...

1078
01:50:01,829 --> 01:50:02,969
No!

1079
01:50:04,765 --> 01:50:05,935
No!

1080
01:50:11,338 --> 01:50:13,558
Let us finish it, Rafael.

1081
01:50:14,174 --> 01:50:15,844
Let us finish what we started...

1082
01:50:16,143 --> 01:50:18,013
the night Esperanza died.

1083
01:50:19,513 --> 01:50:20,742
Drop your sword...

1084
01:50:20,981 --> 01:50:23,791
or I will have no choice,
but to have you shot.

1085
01:50:24,251 --> 01:50:26,391
Even in the presence of my daughter.

1086
01:50:29,890 --> 01:50:31,500
Please.

1087
01:50:46,773 --> 01:50:48,323
They were flowers.

1088
01:50:48,675 --> 01:50:50,485
Romneya.

1089
01:50:57,017 --> 01:50:58,217
Rafael...

1090
01:51:01,054 --> 01:51:02,544
she knows.

1091
01:53:11,718 --> 01:53:12,827
Water!

1092
01:53:48,455 --> 01:53:49,535
Lock them up!

1093
01:54:46,046 --> 01:54:47,626
The fuses are burning. Hurry it up.

1094
01:54:52,652 --> 01:54:53,852
Let's go.

1095
01:55:16,943 --> 01:55:18,023
Wait here.

1096
01:55:28,088 --> 01:55:29,898
Secure the wagon. Stay alert.

1097
01:57:00,113 --> 01:57:01,573
De la Vega.

1098
01:57:02,549 --> 01:57:03,839
Rafael.

1099
01:58:17,857 --> 01:58:19,117
Only one question.

1100
01:58:23,496 --> 01:58:24,426
Really?

1101
01:58:24,631 --> 01:58:25,681
What is that?

1102
01:58:30,270 --> 01:58:32,290
How would you like your
remains displayed?

1103
02:00:03,029 --> 02:00:05,309
Now I'm free...to kill you.

1104
02:00:05,699 --> 02:00:06,839
No!

1105
02:00:13,640 --> 02:00:15,160
Drop the sword.

1106
02:00:15,975 --> 02:00:17,025
Drop it.

1107
02:00:26,753 --> 02:00:29,123
You really think
I would have killed my own child?

1108
02:00:32,325 --> 02:00:33,085
No!

1109
02:00:54,981 --> 02:00:56,001
Did you miss me?

1110
02:01:19,973 --> 02:01:21,583
Elena! Get them out!

1111
02:01:29,616 --> 02:01:32,516
"M"...for Murrieta.

1112
02:01:33,186 --> 02:01:34,766
Two men.

1113
02:01:35,555 --> 02:01:36,635
One death!

1114
02:02:38,284 --> 02:02:39,744
You're doin’ well.

1115
02:02:40,119 --> 02:02:42,429
Your brother would have
shot himself by now.

1116
02:04:38,237 --> 02:04:39,547
Alejandro.

1117
02:05:55,681 --> 02:05:57,491
ls it finished?

1118
02:05:58,551 --> 02:06:02,421
Yes, Don Diego...it's finished.

1119
02:06:04,624 --> 02:06:06,464
Not for Zorro.

1120
02:06:07,226 --> 02:06:10,476
There will be other days,
other battles to fight.

1121
02:06:11,297 --> 02:06:13,906
It is your curse and destiny.

1122
02:06:17,036 --> 02:06:19,086
My beautiful Elena.

1123
02:06:21,974 --> 02:06:24,344
The world is a strange place.

1124
02:06:26,646 --> 02:06:29,516
To have found you at last,
only to lose you again.

1125
02:06:29,982 --> 02:06:31,792
You will never lose me...

1126
02:06:33,319 --> 02:06:34,989
Father.

1127
02:06:38,791 --> 02:06:40,341
Elena...

1128
02:06:43,062 --> 02:06:44,791
you are like your mother.

1129
02:06:46,599 --> 02:06:48,299
Same eyes.

1130
02:06:49,001 --> 02:06:50,841
Same mouth.

1131
02:06:51,671 --> 02:06:53,311
Same spirit.

1132
02:06:58,344 --> 02:06:59,984
Alejandro...

1133
02:07:02,915 --> 02:07:04,495
Elena.

1134
02:07:24,904 --> 02:07:26,804
And so it was.

1135
02:07:27,540 --> 02:07:29,650
Lightning split the sky...

1136
02:07:30,009 --> 02:07:31,909
thunder shook the Earth.

1137
02:07:32,512 --> 02:07:35,232
Then, all was quiet.

1138
02:07:37,316 --> 02:07:39,096
The great warrior known as...

1139
02:07:39,418 --> 02:07:42,788
Zotro...was gone.

1140
02:07:43,890 --> 02:07:46,140
People of the land gave him
a hero's funeral,

1141
02:07:46,526 --> 02:07:49,076
the largest anyone had ever seen.

1142
02:07:49,695 --> 02:07:51,625
They came from far and wide

1143
02:07:51,964 --> 02:07:55,124
to say farewell to the brave
and noble champion.

1144
02:07:58,704 --> 02:08:00,754
But don't worry, little Joaquin.

1145
02:08:02,108 --> 02:08:04,538
Whenever great
deeds are remembered...

1146
02:08:04,977 --> 02:08:07,087
your grandfather will live on.

1147
02:08:08,915 --> 02:08:12,105
For there must always,
always be a Zorro.

1148
02:08:12,685 --> 02:08:17,225
And someday, when he's needed,
we will see him again.

1149
02:08:18,257 --> 02:08:22,597
On his fearsome steed, Tornado,
riding like the wind,

1150
02:08:23,429 --> 02:08:25,769
his sword blazing in the sun.

1151
02:08:26,499 --> 02:08:27,579
Leaping...

1152
02:08:27,800 --> 02:08:28,440
. .
jumping...

1153
02:08:28,601 --> 02:08:29,911
swinging through the air.

1154
02:08:30,169 --> 02:08:33,858
Fighting like a lion,
fighting like a tiger, fighting...

1155
02:08:41,314 --> 02:08:43,364
as safely as possible.

1156
02:08:45,184 --> 02:08:47,904
Is this your idea
of putting the baby to sleep?

1157
02:08:55,328 --> 02:08:57,168
Sleep tight, my son.

1158
02:09:04,170 --> 02:09:06,450
When I sleep I will dream of this...

1159
02:09:06,839 --> 02:09:09,499
dashing rogue, Zorro.

1160
02:09:10,543 --> 02:09:12,822
But what face shall I give him?

1161
02:09:14,247 --> 02:09:16,857
He has been
many different men, but...

1162
02:09:17,750 --> 02:09:19,830
he has loved you as all of them.

1163
02:09:25,224 --> 02:09:27,474
How can I refuse such a man?

1164
02:09:29,395 --> 02:09:31,535
Do you know where I might find him?

1165
02:09:32,732 --> 02:09:34,402
You know Zorro...

1166
02:09:34,967 --> 02:09:36,897
he could be anywhere.

1167
02:09:53,653 --> 02:09:58,163
There, there, my darling.

